cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SI

This paper deals with testing and learning causal models, which are often studied in the machine learning community. The use of interventions and the focus on sample/time/intervention efficiency suggest that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of subadditivity inequality and the focus on information theory suggest that cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category. The use of graphs and the focus on bounded in-degree and confounded components suggest that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may also be a relevant category. Finally, the focus on causal models and their applications suggest that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) may also be a relevant category.
